Working with MRI Data: Applying a Mask¶

Applying a mask to an MRI image is a great way to separate the voxels (3-D pixels) we are interested in for data analysis, from the voxels we are not interested in. In this assignment, I wanted to apply a mask that would separate the voxels of the brain from the voxels of the black background, in order to examine the brain activity later. The process of applying a mask is demonstrated below.

Import Necessary Packages¶

In [2]:
import imageio

Apply the Mask¶

In [7]:
brain_mask = np.where(brain_img > 125, 1, 0)
plt.imshow(brain_mask, cmap = 'gray')
plt.axis('off')
plt.show()
